area_name: Swedish House Mafia Boulders / Hill Top Area.

content.description: Can be started a couple different ways. Climb into the V and top out.
content.location: Located on north side of formation. Just right of Me Nombre Es Thor.

content.description: Ascend straight up center of the beautiful blank canvis, that makes up the south side of formation. Excellent edging and crimps to a cool mantle.
content.location: Located on south side of formation, just left of the Blue Eyed Arete.

content.description: One of the best arête climbs at Melrose and on this formation. Start low on awkward barn doory side pulls and poor feet. Core dependent move, will get you to the slapping sloper mid way on arête. Now crank hard to crimp up and left to stand up and mantle.
content.location: Located on East Side of Formation. Swedish Gangster is the obvious arête making up the left side of the Scandinavian Chimney.

content.description: Swedish Fish is an awesome, steep, crimpy, side pull test piece. Thought provoking and powerful for how straight forward it looks
content.protection: Ok landing, ankle busting flake at start. Pad.
content.location: Located on east side of formation, just right of Scandinavian Chimney. Start off ankle busting flake.

content.description: One of the original old school climbs at Melrose. Climb the obvious flared off-width chimney. Clean and enjoyable.
content.protection: Kinda high ball, good landing, pad.
content.location: Obvious flared chimney on east side of formation.

content.description: My name is Thor, climbs the technical lichen coverd slab between Swedish Fish and Viking in America.
content.location: Located on north side of formation just right of Swedish Fish.

content.description: Climb crimpy and edgy face features to top. Crux comes probably after first move, establishing the following sequence.
content.location: Located on the East  face. Euro Squeeze ascends the face between Swedish Gangster and Blue Eyed Arête.

climbs.name: Blue Eyed Arête AKA The Blue Arete.

content.description: The other classic arête on this formation. Can be climbed on either side. Great intro to Arête climbing.
content.location: South east arête on SHM Boulders. Easily seen driving down entrance of sport park to you left once you pass houses.

content.description: Super burl compression moves off overhanging arête and terrible slopers. Sit start low and squeeze/hug your way to the top.
content.location: Beowulf climbs the obvious low ball, overhanging, blunt arête, that makes up south west side of formation. Just left of Swedish Mariachi.
